1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Bright ice reflects sunlight; dark water absorbs it.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,400
What happens next?

3
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:06,800
This is called the albedo effect.

4
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:10,400
More ice means less absorption, keeping our planet cool.

5
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,400
But as ice melts, dark oceans emerge, soaking up heat.

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,600
The cycle begins.

7
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,800
Research shows that this albedo feedback accelerates warming.

8
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,400
It’s a tipping point.

9
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Melting ice isn't just a loss; it fuels a hotter future for all of us.

10
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,400
Stay informed and take action.

11
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:31,200
Follow for more insights on climate science!
